!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

ethnic /ˈɛθnɪk/

1. ADJ Ethnic means connected with or relating to different racial or cultural groups of people. 种族的 

例： ...a survey of Britain's ethnic minorities. …对英国少数民族的一项调查。 

2. ethnically ADV 种族上地 

例： ...a predominantly young, ethnically mixed audience. …一群大部分为年轻的、包含不同种族的观众。 

3. ADJ You can use ethnic to describe people who belong to a particular racial or cultural group but who, usually, do not live in the country where most members of that group live. 少数民族的 [ADJ n] 

例： There are still several million ethnic Germans in Russia. 在俄罗斯仍有几百万德国族裔。 

4. ethnically ADV 少数民族地 [ADV adj] 

例： ...a large ethnically Albanian population. …大量阿尔巴尼亚族人口。 

5. ADJ Ethnic clothing, music, or food is characteristic of the traditions of a particular ethnic group, and different from what is usually found in modern Western culture. 具有民族特色的 

例： ...a magnificent range of ethnic fabrics. …各色各样具有民族特色的织物。

</div>

